                <h2 data-uuid="f78c59645437404ebcfc28fc0956d9ec"> Document-Based Investigation</h2>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="4138ad0b3d4d4df8b58358647fdb3de8">Part 2: Write an Argument</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="871ce1feb70647589c6fb1d5968a2e8b">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="bf1b13f954e044bf8b2c9cfe1c50786d">During
                the 1960s, the United States was committed to the Cold War policy of stopping
                communism worldwide. When communists threatened to take control of the
                Southeast Asian nation of Vietnam, the United States sent troops to stop them.
                Initially, a majority of Americans supported the Vietnam War; after years of
                fighting, however, many began to call for an end to U.S. involvement.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="36908750f095422e8907dcb6ae7c2875">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="7ea7ea3ef8ec4b11949dfe0718f7b845">Was the United States right to become involved
                in the Vietnam War? Did the U.S. achieve its goals there? Did the effects of
                the war justify the costs? Write an argument either supporting or opposing
                American involvement in the war.</p>
            <p data-uuid="62b3b220bfcf4a4b9ed43af42cb3f55f">Complete
                the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="c8f758b603904b259b53b6e52d9d39d3">
                <li data-uuid="82678aa49c0345d8a20c0ae62b1c60dd">Review your notes
                    and sources before you start writing.</li>
                <li data-uuid="1fefbe775cf040bfaa12a87385965950">
                    Use at least two
                    of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic with relevant, well-chosen
                    text or visual evidence from the documents.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="996f1a2dc78b4ae3993b24b3776d76f9">
                    Cite specific text
                    or visual evidence from each of the sources in your response.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="46d2e61e7b8545768455463ef34160db">
                    Plan your essay so
                    that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a
                    concluding paragraph.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="14df75313e3d4fcaba1e386fcd32576b">&#160;Clearly state your claim, or position on the topic, and
                    consider any opposing claims.</li>
                <li data-uuid="8c7f55de19d04d9e9288a75b1f0bb23e">Support your claim with logical reasoning and evidence from
                    credible sources.</li>
                <li data-uuid="413f2e41637841329cff29fc0f756205">Organize your essay in a clear and logical way and use
                    linking words and phrases to clarify the relationship between claims and
                    counterclaims, as well as between ideas.</li>
                <li data-uuid="d745f04d12d2429db3a1726db9f71f72">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the
                    argument you present.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
